# PART 1: FILE HANDLING SYSTEM\
\
## Two Modes of File Integration\
\
### Mode 1: Smart Reference (Default)\
\
Files stay where they are. FlowState indexes and describes them.\
\
**User Flow:**\
\
1. User drags file onto project/component/problem\
1. FlowState prompts: \'93Describe this file (optional)\'94\
1. User adds description OR clicks \'93Let Claude describe it\'94\
1. Claude reads file, generates:\
- Summary description\
- Key content locations (page numbers, line numbers)\
- Suggested tags/categories\
1. File reference stored in database with metadata\
1. File remains at original location OR copied to project bundle (user choice)\
\
**Use Case:** \'93I have a 50-page spec PDF. I want to reference pages 12-15 when working on the auth component.\'94\
\
### Mode 2: Full Extraction\
\
Claude breaks the file down into structured database records.\
\
**User Flow:**\
\
1. User drags file onto project\
1. User selects \'93Extract to Database\'94\
1. Claude parses entire file and creates:\
- Learnings (insights, patterns, best practices found)\
- Problems (issues, bugs, challenges mentioned)\
- Todos (action items, requirements)\
- Changes (decisions, version history mentioned)\
- Components (system parts, modules described)\
1. User reviews extracted records before confirming\
1. Original file can be kept as reference or discarded\
\
**Use Case:** \'93I have meeting notes from last week. Extract all the decisions and action items into FlowState.\'94\
