## Git Operations\
\
### Initial Setup (First Machine)\
\
```bash\
# FlowState does this automatically on first run\
cd ~/FlowState-Data\
git init\
git add .\
git commit -m "FlowState initialized"\
\
# User clicks "Connect to GitHub" in settings\
# FlowState creates private repo and pushes\
git remote add origin https://github.com/username/flowstate-data.git\
git push -u origin main\
```\
\
### Sync Operation\
\
**\'93Sync\'94 button performs:**\
\
```bash\
git add .\
git commit -m "FlowState sync - [timestamp]"\
git pull --rebase origin main\
git push origin main\
```\
\
### Setup on Second Machine\
\
**User clicks \'93Connect Existing\'94 and enters repo URL:**\
\
```bash\
git clone https://github.com/username/flowstate-data.git ~/FlowState-Data\
```\
\
## Conflict Handling\
\
**Strategy:** Last-write-wins with backup\
\
1. On sync conflict, FlowState:\
- Saves local database as `database.sqlite.local-backup-[timestamp]`\
- Accepts remote version\
- Notifies user: \'93Sync conflict detected. Your local changes backed up.\'94\
1. User can:\
- Review backup and manually merge if needed\
- Or just continue (most conflicts are benign)\
\
**Prevention:**\
\
- FlowState shows \'93Last synced from [device] at [time]\'94\
- Warning if another device synced recently: \'93Mac synced 5 min ago. Pull latest first?\'94\
