# Working with Files\
\
## Adding Files\
Drag any file onto FlowState to attach it to your project.\
\
## Two Ways to Handle Files\
\
### Reference Mode (Default)\
- File stays where it is (or copies to project bundle)\
- Claude generates a description and indexes key locations\
- Search finds content inside your files\
- Perfect for: specs, documentation, reference material\
\
### Extract Mode\
- Claude reads the entire file\
- Creates structured records from the content\
- Decisions become Changes\
- Issues become Problems  \
- Insights become Learnings\
- Perfect for: meeting notes, brainstorm docs, imported content\
\
## Supported File Types\
- Documents: PDF, DOCX, TXT, MD\
- Images: PNG, JPG, GIF (with OCR)\
- Code: Any text-based code file\
- Data: CSV, JSON, XML\
\
## Finding Content\
- \uc0\u8984 F: Search current view\
- \uc0\u8984 \u8679 F: Search inside all files\
- Click any search result to jump to the exact location\
```\
